703
01:17:19,523 --> 01:17:20,301
Not this ones.

704
01:17:25,035 --> 01:17:26,010
It's all I have...

705
01:17:27,435 --> 01:17:30,630
I wish I had more... for you.

706
01:17:32,726 --> 01:17:36,871
Maybe if I was a famous baseball
player, or a guy who wore a suit to work...

707
01:17:39,016 --> 01:17:41,352
I would have more to leave you.

708
01:17:41,477 --> 01:17:43,753
But, you can be one of those
people if you want.

709
01:17:46,980 --> 01:17:49,009
Yeah.

710
01:17:50,219 --> 01:17:52,878
Just promise me that when you get older,
you’ll take good care of your mom.

711
01:17:54,407 --> 01:17:57,076
And... I don't know...

712
01:17:58,244 --> 01:17:59,860
That you’ll always try
to do the right thing.

713
01:18:04,126 --> 01:18:06,670
I love you very much, Shane.

714
01:18:09,047 --> 01:18:11,633
Maybe I never said that
enough...

715
01:18:11,850 --> 01:18:13,282
Maybe I did,
I don’t even know.

716
01:18:14,186 --> 01:18:15,587
That probably means I didn’t.

717
01:18:23,780 --> 01:18:28,994
I’m sorry, Linda.
I should have listened to you.

718
01:19:32,685 --> 01:19:33,508
You’re not dead.

719
01:19:34,327 --> 01:19:35,672
Hello? Hello?!

720
01:19:36,105 --> 01:19:38,941
- Where is money?
- I don’t know.

721
01:19:39,066 --> 01:19:40,548
- What don’t know?
- I don’t know where it is.

722
01:19:40,769 --> 01:19:42,699
- Liar!
- I’m not lying! I swear.

723
01:19:42,700 --> 01:19:45,735
- Swear?
- I swear. I’m telling the truth.

724
01:19:45,736 --> 01:19:47,046
- From Embassy
- I can’t!

725
01:19:47,047 --> 01:19:48,259
- You get money now!
- I can’t!

726
01:19:48,495 --> 01:19:49,973
- You will!
- I need more time. Please.

727
01:19:49,974 --> 01:19:50,879
No more time!

728
01:19:50,914 --> 01:19:53,750
There’s sand pouring in here.
It’s everywhere. Let me out of here.

729
01:19:53,876 --> 01:19:56,208
- I will get you the money.
- You show blood.

730
01:19:56,683 --> 01:19:58,829
- What?
- You show blood, they give money.

731
01:19:59,968 --> 01:20:03,444
- You cut finger, send video.
- I’m not doing that.

732
01:20:03,688 --> 01:20:04,756
- No?
- No.

733
01:20:04,803 --> 01:20:05,504
That’s right, no.

734
01:20:05,586 --> 01:20:08,533
You let me out of here, and I’ll cut
off my whole God damn hand if you want.

735
01:20:08,830 --> 01:20:09,653
You have wife?

736
01:20:09,788 --> 01:20:12,836
Yes, I do. And a son. A young son.
I want to see them. Please, sir.

737
01:20:12,871 --> 01:20:15,417
- Sir? - Yes. Sir. I say that
out of respect... to you.

738
01:20:15,919 --> 01:20:20,088
243 East Walnut Street.
Hastings, Michigan. U.S.A.

739
01:20:20,089 --> 01:20:25,590
- That’s my... why did you say that?
- You show blood... or they show blood.

740
01:20:26,409 --> 01:20:27,137
No.

741
01:20:27,822 --> 01:20:30,425
That’s... you’re lying.
You can’t get to them.

742
01:20:30,839 --> 01:20:31,667
- No?
- No.

743
01:20:31,908 --> 01:20:33,583
No. You’re peasants,
you're fucking criminals, that’s all.

744
01:20:33,892 --> 01:20:34,809
You don’t even know
where Michigan is.

745
01:20:35,334 --> 01:20:37,252
Detroit. Ann Arbor.

746
01:20:37,377 --> 01:20:40,162
You looked at a map.
You looked at a map.

747
01:20:40,601 --> 01:20:42,044
You show blood, or they show blood.

748
01:20:42,897 --> 01:20:44,066
Send video by five minutes.

749
01:20:58,174 --> 01:21:01,251
<i>Hi, this is Linda. Please leave a
message. Thanks and have a great day.</i>

750
01:21:01,436 --> 01:21:05,065
Linda, listen to me, you and Shane
have to go somewhere... Okay?

751
01:21:05,190 --> 01:21:07,692
Do not go back to the house.
Do not go back to the house.

752
01:21:07,817 --> 01:21:11,574
...he knows where you live.
He stole my license.

753
01:21:11,575 --> 01:21:13,807
Go to the Sheriff's station if you
have to, just don’t go home.

754
01:21:27,289 --> 01:21:30,409
<i>This is Daniel Brenner. Please
leave a message at the tone.</i>

755
01:21:30,899 --> 01:21:32,563
Brenner, where are you?!
The guy is still alive!

756
01:21:33,188 --> 01:21:35,026
He just called me!
He's still alive!

757
01:21:39,875 --> 01:21:44,103
They can’t find them.
They... can’t. There’s no way.

758
01:21:45,206 --> 01:21:46,976
No, no, no, no,

759
01:22:03,059 --> 01:22:03,981
<i>My name is Pamela Lutti.</i>

760
01:22:05,443 --> 01:22:11,021
<i>I’m a food service worker at F.O.B. Anaconda,
employed by Crestin, Roland and Thomas.</i>

761
01:22:13,619 --> 01:22:15,676
<i>My captor's requests for ransom
have gone unanswered, and...</i>

762
01:22:16,218 --> 01:22:17,095
<i>Please... no!</i>

763
01:24:01,974 --> 01:24:04,047
Paul.
Are you okay?

764
01:24:22,336 --> 01:24:24,063
- Yeah?
- Paul, it’s Brenner.

765
01:24:25,222 --> 01:24:28,141
- Are you there, Paul?
- I’m... here.

766
01:24:28,229 --> 01:24:30,766
We’re coming for you now. You hear
me? We know where you are.

767
01:24:31,297 --> 01:24:33,595
- You’re coming?
- We are, Paul. We’re almost there now.

768
01:24:34,122 --> 01:24:34,832
How do you know?

